cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "VoiceInvariantBench: A Speech-to-Action Conservation Benchmark for Voice Agents"
message: "If you use this benchmark, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "VoiceInvariantBench Contributors"
    given-names: ""
version: "1.1.1"
date-released: "2026-05-27"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/EmmanuelleB985/voice-invariant-bench"
abstract: |
  VoiceInvariantBench measures whether voice agents preserve critical
  spoken values — dates, times, amounts, addresses, postcodes, codes —
  from audio through to final tool-action state. The headline metric is
  the Speech-to-Action Conservation Rate (SACR). The benchmark is
  stack-decomposable: TTS, ASR, and agent reasoning failures can be
  attributed separately, enabling component-level procurement decisions
  that single-number evals cannot support.
keywords:
  - voice agents
  - benchmark
  - speech recognition
  - tool use
  - safety
  - llm evaluation
